description:
&lt;p&gt;The Mid Yorkshire Trust is currently inviting applications for enthusiastic Band 5 Registered Nurses or Operating Department Practitioners (ODP) to join our friendly and forward thinking theatre team.This opportunity would suit both newly qualified and experienced applicants as an excellent mentoring and/or preceptorship programme is provided for the successful candidates. Our dedicated education team support and enable the professional development of all colleagues and students and have close long standing links with the local university.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust has 25 general theatres and 3 obstetric theatres across 3 hospital sites in Wakefield, Pontefract and Dewsbury, providing a dynamic and challenging range of clinical specialities and service demands. All acute surgery is now centralised on the Pinderfields site in Wakefield.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking highly motivated team players who are professional, inspire others and embrace change. A flexible, can do attitude is essential. If you are keen to build on your theatre knowledge and skills and are committed to developing and enhancing the quality of patient care within this specialist environment, then this is an excellent opportunity for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full and part time posts are available which includes a commitment to night rotation, bank holiday and weekend working and participation in an On Call rota&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information / informal visit please contact :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alison Hutton, Professional Lead for Acute &amp; Emergency Theatres 01924 542088 Jackie Elder, Lead Clinical Educator (Theatres) 07825113733.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
